      </m:math> </equation><para id="import-auto-id2072030">(3) Calculate to find the frequency: 2,500,325 Hz.</para><para id="import-auto-id2956450">
      <title>Solution for (b)</title>
    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2677100">(1) Identify knowns:</para>
    <list id="eip-353"><item>The blood acts as a moving source.</item>
<item>The microphone acts as a stationary observer.</item>
<item>The frequency leaving the blood is 2,500,325 Hz, but it is shifted upward as given by<equation id="eip-id2042853"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>obs</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>s</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mfenced open="(" close=")"><m:mfrac><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>w</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>w</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">–</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>b</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:mfenced></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></equation><para id="eip-748"><m:math><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mn>obs</m:mn></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math> is the frequency received by the speaker-microphone.</para></item>
<item>The source velocity is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi fontstyle="italic">v</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>b</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>.</item>
<item>The minus sign is used because the motion is toward the observer.</item>
</list><para id="import-auto-id3172720">The minus sign is used because the motion is toward the observer.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2446121">(2) Enter the given values into the equation:</para><equation id="eip-953"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>

              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
